Nigerian radio broadcaster, Daddy Freeze, has taken to social media to air his opinion, following the allegations of the friends of demised gospel singer, Osinachi Nwachukwu, that the singer died as a result of the beatings and abuses she received from her husband.
Recall that Nigerian gospel singer, Osinachi Nwachukwu, reportedly died on Friday, in a hospital bed, at the federal capital territory, Abuja, following her battle with an undisclosed illness.
However, following the gospel singer’s demise, her friends took to social media to react, as they revealed that Osinachi Nwachukwu allegedly died of domestic violence, adding that her husband was always beating and abusing her at home.
The singer’s friends further went ahead to reveal that Osinachi Nwachukwu, despite been abuse by her husband, never mentioned it to people, including her pastor, Paul Eneche, adding that she was trying to protect her husband.
Here are their posts below;
However, following such allegations, Nigerian On-Air-Personality (OAP), Daddy Freeze, took to his official Instagram page to react, as he stated that if the allegations are true, then it confirms what he has been teaching all along with regards to Nigerians leaving an abusive marriage.
Daddy Freeze further went ahead to state that despite his teachings on why people should leave a bad marriage, many people still refer to him as an Antichrist, adding that if Osinachi Nwachukwu had listened to him 3 years ago, she would have been alive and healthy today.
Daddy Freeze finally revealed that many people that are considering endurance in their marriages are prone to committing suicide.
